{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014zZ6YmqqpaUJH6pmvDCMrT","type":"tool_result","content":"   495→\n   496→### `cloche stop`\n   497→\n   498→```\n   499→cloche stop <run-id>\n   500→```\n   501→\n   502→### `cloche delete`\n   503→\n   504→```\n   505→cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   506→```\n   507→\n   508→Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   509→\n   510→### `cloche health`\n   511→\n   512→```\n   513→cloche health\n   514→```\n   515→\n   516→Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   517→\n   518→### `cloche get`\n   519→\n   520→```\n   521→cloche get <key>\n   522→```\n   523→\n   524→Get a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   525→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   526→the current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   527→\n   528→### `cloche set`\n   529→\n   530→```\n   531→cloche set <key> <value>\n   532→```\n   533→\n   534→Set a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   535→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   536→the current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   537→\n   538→### `cloche tasks`\n   539→\n   540→```\n   541→cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   542→```\n   543→\n   544→Show the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"33b01f83-760e-4d97-bd87-ba437b18f7d3","uuid":"b7803d06-a500-44c2-9999-98cba774c818","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche get`\n\n```\ncloche get <key>\n```\n\nGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n\n### `cloche set`\n\n```\ncloche set <key> <value>\n```\n\nSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n\n### `cloche tasks`\n\n```\ncloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n```\n\nShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays","numLines":50,"startLine":495,"totalLines":630}}}
