{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CpV6kfSKKN7rPkFuLEy5nr","type":"tool_result","content":"   590→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   591→| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   592→| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   593→| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   594→| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   595→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   596→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   597→| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   598→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   599→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   600→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   601→\n   602→### Client Configuration\n   603→\n   604→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   605→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   606→| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   607→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   608→\n   609→## Dockerfile Requirements\n   610→\n   611→The container image must have:\n   612→- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   613→- `git` installed\n   614→- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   615→- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   616→- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   617→\n   618→## Build Commands\n   619→\n   620→```\n   621→make build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   622→make test           # Run all tests\n   623→make test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   624→make lint           # Run go vet\n   625→make proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   626→make docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   627→make install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   628→make clean          # Remove bin/\n   629→```\n   630→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"33b01f83-760e-4d97-bd87-ba437b18f7d3","uuid":"19670472-9ddd-4b71-9e73-8b220a6bc84f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":41,"startLine":590,"totalLines":630}}}
